result.execSummary:
The defendant Traveon D Leavell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Bail motion by defense argued and granted by the Court.  The Court modifies (lowers) bail to $750.00.  Justice Point Supervision removed as a condition of bail.

Defendant Traveon D Leavell in court with attorney Bernard S. Stein.  Defendant Traveon D Leavell in custody.  
Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Amended Information filed 7-06-15.  Defense counsel acknowledged receipt of a copy of the Amended Information, waived its reading and entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the defendant.  

Charge amended to:

COUNT 1:  MISDEMEANOR BATTERY- PTAC, AS A PARTY TO A CRIME, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 940.19(1), 939.51(3)(a), 939.05 a Class A Misdemeanor
COUNT 2:  THEFT (VALUE NOT EXCEEDING $2500)- PTAC, AS A PARTY TO A CRIME, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.20(1)(a) and (3)(a), 939.51(3)(a), 939.05 , a Class A Misdemeanor  

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

As to both counts:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was sworn and examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The Court does not accept statement of facts filed by defense as factual basis for the plea.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Matter adjourned to allow the state to effectuate victim notification.  Jury trial date of 7-08-15 removed from the calendar at this time. Filed, Statement of Facts in Support of Guilty Pleas.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for July 20, 2015 at 08:30 am.
